added.title: The Skull
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make friends with classmate Clayton, a compulsive liar who can shape-change!

added.title: Bear Flu
added.description: The Bears become terribly ill and Chloe takes it upon herself to take care of them. But things get tricky when word of the Bears' sickness goes viral.

added.title: The Audition
added.description: The Bears audition to be the next mascot for their favorite cereal. They get so caught up in the process that their competitiveness gets the best of them.

added.title: Captain Craboo
added.description: The Bears are reunited with their pet crab, Captain Craboo. But after an unfortunate run-in with Nom Nom, the Bears may lose their pet forever.

added.title: Baby Bears on a Plane
added.description: The Baby Bears have an adventure in the sky while aboard a plane to Sweden. But when the baby Bears are forced to sit in different sections of the plan, things get a bit haywire for everyone on board.

added.title: Yuri and the Bear
added.description: Baby Ice Bear lives alone in the arctic and meets a mysterious man named Yuri. Together they help each other survive the cold environment.

added.title: Our Stuff
added.description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Pet Shop
added.description: Pet Shop tells the tale of where the Baby Bears once lived, and after a run-in with a video crew shooting a Sarah McLachlan-type animal adoption video, almost seized an opportunity to find a home separated from each other.

added.title: The Final Book
added.description: The last book of Kelsey's favorite fantasy series goes missing from the library, so Craig decides to help her solve the mystery of who took it.

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP run afoul of some no-good teenage witches and are cursed! Lousy teenagers!

added.title: Lost in the Sewer
added.description: Craig agrees to help The Sewer Queen map the sewers, but he quickly finds himself in over his head.

added.title: Pajama Pajimjams
added.description: Oscar pretends to be a talking pair of pajamas named "Jimjams" to make his friend Pajamas happy.

added.title: Feeling Spacey
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog arrive on a planet that has no emotions.

added.title: Ghost the Boy
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog befriend a ghost who can't remember who he is.

added.title: The Basketball Liaries
added.description: With the help from Basketball, Oscar makes an impressive shot that scores him a spot on the Gold League.

added.title: Popular Banana Split
added.description: Hedgehog and Max discover a tiny high school when they are accidentally shrunk by a science experiment.

added.title: It's My Party
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog plan a surprise birthday party for Susie.

added.title: Moon Problems
added.description: The Moon gets sad when Oscar loses his friendship bracelet.

added.title: Monster Visit
added.description: The monsters get nervous when their Godmonster comes for a visit.

added.title: Ice Cream Headache
added.description: The campers get magical powers from the witches supply of magic ice cream.

added.title: Pepper's Blanket Is Missing
added.description: Pepper's blanket goes missing at a cabin sleepover.

added.title: Hedgehog Werewolf
added.description: Hedgehog gets bit by a cute puppy and is starting to act strange.

added.title: Mr. Softball
added.description: Susie challenges the campers to a game of softball to get out of doing a chore.

added.title: Fuzzy Pink Time Babies
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog learn how to stop time.

added.title: Ghost Fly
added.description: Jake and the tree house are haunted by a vengeful spectre.

added.title: Nightmare Hospital
added.description: Steven and Connie sneak into a hospital to recover Rose's Sword.

added.title: Flirty Phantom
added.description: Lost in Transylberia, the Warriors come to a haunted house for help and meet a young ghost lady inside that wants to spend the rest of her afterlife with Prohyas!

added.title: Phased and Confused
added.description: When members of the Justice League are affected by the Phantom Zone ray and become phantom-like, their only hope for freedom is to somehow get a message to Booster Gold.

added.title: Be a Team
added.description: Mr. Gar brings in some team building experts to help KO, Enid and Rad.

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: When Master Frown's head is stuck on Unikitty's butt, she vows to help him get his own body back, but first, she has to attend to her nice princess duties! But sharing a body with Master Frown can get pretty complicated, especially when Master Frown has his own agenda.

added.title: License to Punch
added.description: Hawkodile's caught by the Action Police for bodyguarding without an Action License. He's can't protect the kingdom or do anything rad until he does, but the test at the DMV (The Department of Mayhem and Violence) is for nerds! Forced to retire his gloves, Hawkodile struggles to live a life without punching, so Unikitty vows to help her friend contain his urge to be action-y and study for the test. But there's more to the test than meets the eye.

added.title: Dancer Danger
added.description: Unikingdom's throwing a kingdom-wide dance, a fun event where everyone dresses up and busts a move. Everyone's excited... except for Richard, who's terrified to let loose and feel his inner groove. Unikitty knows Rick needs to express himself but can she and the others convince him to break out of his shell with some minor robotic body enhancements?

added.title: Reunited
added.description: Steven brings everyone together for a special reunion.

added.title: Lion 4: Alternate Ending
added.description: Lion coughs up a magical key, and Steven goes on a quest to find what it unlocks.

added.title: A New Life
added.description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

added.title: The Perfect Team
added.description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

added.title: Tips
added.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: Apple's in Trouble
added.description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

added.title: 4 on 1
added.description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: Bottle Catch
added.description: Apple and Onion's favorite game attracts some unexpected attention.

added.title: Pancake's Bus Tour
added.description: Apple and Onion go on a guided bus tour as part of their plan to get Apple's shoe back.

added.title: Block Party
added.description: Apple and Onion have to outwit a mean duck who's taken over their building's roof.

added.title: Talent Show
added.description: Clarence throws a big talent show in his yard to showcase all the fun hidden talents of his friends. But when Brady claims he's talentless, Clarence sets out to prove that everyone has something special to share!

added.title: RC Car
added.description: Clarence spends a day outside with his toy RC Car, which he names Carla. Eventually convinced Carla has a mind of her own, he decides to follow her to new adventures. Will Clarence's car chase get in the way of Jeff and Sumo's plans for the day?

added.title: Dog King Clarence
added.description: When Clarence's neighbor Gale recruits him to dog sit for her, he knows it will be a breeze, being the self-proclaimed "Dog King," Clarence knows all there is to know about pups. Nevertheless, Gale's dog proves to be a little more challenging than he expects!

added.title: Trampoline
added.description: Mary buys a new trampoline for the family, but an accident lands her on the couch for a while. Determined to fight the boredom of being stuck indoors, she discovers her neighbor may be hiding something exciting.

added.title: Clarence the Movie
added.description: When Clarence starts to play around with his home video camera, he becomes increasingly drawn into the world of filmmaking. From talking toys, to real actors, to documentary subjects, Clarence is determined to find the right style to tell his story!

added.title: Belson Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: Clarence is in disbelief when he learns his best friend Belson has a new girlfriend named Pipi. But when he observes their less than romantic behavior, he decides that he needs to teach them the ways of love to help keep their fling afloat!

added.title: Etiquette Clarence
added.description: Clarence submits a short story into a creative writing contest, and he's overjoyed when he learns he's accepted as a finalist! But when Jeff finds out Clarence has to attend a formal dinner, he fixates on transforming the messy Clarence into a proper gentleman.

added.title: Video Store
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo visit their local video store to rent a movie, but discover it's all rented out! Each of them have a different idea of what tape to bring home, and must enlist the help of a tie breaker to figure it out.

added.title: Anywhere but Sumo
added.description: When Clarence realizes Sumo has made a new group of friends at his new school, he becomes jealous and confused. Will Clarence accept a school life void of Sumo, or scheme his way into making their friendship work?

added.title: Mojo the Great
added.description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

added.title: Save the Date
added.description: Ms. Keane is nervous about a first date.

added.title: Can't Buy Love
added.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

added.title: Largo
added.description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

added.title: A Slight Hiccup
added.description: The Girls must overcome their supersonic hiccups to stop the Gnat's latest evil plan!

added.title: Cheep Thrills
added.description: After finding a baby monster in the park, Bubbles insists on adopting it without considering the consequences!

added.title: Sick as a Bot
added.description: After the Energon seeking WINGCODE infects the Autobots with a virus, Bulkhead joins Grimlock in his frantic hunt for the Decepticon. But to capture the 'Con, the duo of brawny Bots has to learn to keep their cool and come up with a workable plan.

added.title: Enemy of My Enemy
added.description: When Optimus returns with old friends and dire warnings of a Cybertronian invasion of Earth, the Autobots must split up to defend their old home and their new one, with the Bee Team returning to Cybertron, while Optimus and his All-Stars stay behind to defend against the invasion's advanced force.

added.title: Harley Goes Ape!
added.description: When Gorilla Grodd takes control over Titano, the giant ape, the only person who seems to be able to override his control is the medical worker who nursed him as a chimp. She's now known as Harley Quinn.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Retires
added.description: Uncle Grandpa discovers a new, unusual occupation.

added.title: Moon Breaker
added.description: Optimus Prime arrives to recruit Drift for a special mission, sparking a competition between Sideswipe and Strongarm over who'd be better suited to take Drift's spot. All this while the Autobots venture to the moon to recover a dangerous weapon before Motormaster and his spacefaring Stunticons can get to it.

added.title: Breathing Room
added.description: The tight confines of the caverns has everyone on edge, so Bee goes on a scouting mission, only to be captured by Steeljaw's Decepticons who also manage to capture the squabbling Sideswipe and Strongarm. Fixit, along for the mission, does his best to keep Steeljaw and the 'Cons at bay in the depths of the subway chamber junction while all the captured Autobots work to free themselves and defeat the 'Cons.

added.title: Prisoner Principles
added.description: Strongarm struggles with the correct way to treat a prisoner while also helping the Bee Team keep Steeljaw and his pack from wreaking havoc at a nuclear power plant.
